# --- CORS ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Comma-separated allowlist of frontend origins. Leave unset in dev to mirror
# the request origin. In production, set to e.g.
#   https://crm.example.com,https://staging.crm.example.com
# CORS_ORIGINS=

# --- Persistence (Vercel KV / Upstash Redis) -----------------------------
# Provision Vercel KV from the Vercel dashboard (Storage tab) and link it to
# this project. Vercel will inject these vars automatically. Locally, copy the
# values from `vercel env pull .env.local`. With these unset the app falls back
# to an in-memory store seeded on every cold start.
# KV_REST_API_URL=
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=
# KV_REST_API_READ_ONLY_TOKEN=
# KV_URL=
# Optional: prefix snapshots so multiple environments can share a KV store.
# KV_NAMESPACE=production

# --- Future Postgres migration -------------------------------------------
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/tourism_crm
